29constexpr int64_t kStatisticsTimeoutMs = 8000;
30constexpr int64_t kStatisticsProcessIntervalMs = 1000;
31
32// Number of seconds since 1900 January 1 00:00 GMT (see
33// https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc868).
34constexpr int64_t kNtpJan1970Millisecs = 2'208'988'800'000;
35} // namespace

37StreamStatistician::~StreamStatistician() {}
38
39StreamStatisticianImpl::StreamStatisticianImpl(uint32_t ssrc,
40 Clock* clock,
41 int max_reordering_threshold)
42 : ssrc_(ssrc),
43 clock_(clock),
44 delta_internal_unix_epoch_ms_(clock_->CurrentNtpInMilliseconds() -
45 clock_->TimeInMilliseconds() -
46 kNtpJan1970Millisecs),
47 incoming_bitrate_(kStatisticsProcessIntervalMs,
48 RateStatistics::kBpsScale),
49 max_reordering_threshold_(max_reordering_threshold),
50 enable_retransmit_detection_(false),
51 cumulative_loss_is_capped_(false),
52 jitter_q4_(0),
53 cumulative_loss_(0),
54 cumulative_loss_rtcp_offset_(0),
55 last_receive_time_ms_(0),
56 last_received_timestamp_(0),
57 received_seq_first_(-1),
58 received_seq_max_(-1),
59 last_report_cumulative_loss_(0),
60 last_report_seq_max_(-1) {}
61
62StreamStatisticianImpl::~StreamStatisticianImpl() = default;
63
64bool StreamStatisticianImpl::UpdateOutOfOrder(const RtpPacketReceived& packet,
65 int64_t sequence_number,
66 int64_t now_ms) {
67 // Check if |packet| is second packet of a stream restart.
68 if (received_seq_out_of_order_) {
69 // Count the previous packet as a received; it was postponed below.
70 --cumulative_loss_;
71
72 uint16_t expected_sequence_number = *received_seq_out_of_order_ + 1;
73 received_seq_out_of_order_ = absl::nullopt;
74 if (packet.SequenceNumber() == expected_sequence_number) {
75 // Ignore sequence number gap caused by stream restart for packet loss
76 // calculation, by setting received_seq_max_ to the sequence number just
77 // before the out-of-order seqno. This gives a net zero change of
78 // |cumulative_loss_|, for the two packets interpreted as a stream reset.
79 //
80 // Fraction loss for the next report may get a bit off, since we don't
81 // update last_report_seq_max_ and last_report_cumulative_loss_ in a
82 // consistent way.
83 last_report_seq_max_ = sequence_number - 2;
84 received_seq_max_ = sequence_number - 2;
85 return false;
86 }
87 }
88
89 if (std::abs(sequence_number - received_seq_max_) >
90 max_reordering_threshold_) {
91 // Sequence number gap looks too large, wait until next packet to check
92 // for a stream restart.
93 received_seq_out_of_order_ = packet.SequenceNumber();
94 // Postpone counting this as a received packet until we know how to update
95 // |received_seq_max_|, otherwise we temporarily decrement
96 // |cumulative_loss_|. The
97 // ReceiveStatisticsTest.StreamRestartDoesntCountAsLoss test expects
98 // |cumulative_loss_| to be unchanged by the reception of the first packet
99 // after stream reset.
100 ++cumulative_loss_;
101 return true;
102 }
103
104 if (sequence_number > received_seq_max_)
105 return false;
106
107 // Old out of order packet, may be retransmit.
108 if (enable_retransmit_detection_ && IsRetransmitOfOldPacket(packet, now_ms))
109 receive_counters_.retransmitted.AddPacket(packet);
110 return true;
111}
112
113void StreamStatisticianImpl::UpdateCounters(const RtpPacketReceived& packet) {
114 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(ssrc_, packet.Ssrc());
115 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
116
117 incoming_bitrate_.Update(packet.size(), now_ms);
118 receive_counters_.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms = now_ms;
119 receive_counters_.transmitted.AddPacket(packet);
120 --cumulative_loss_;
121
122 int64_t sequence_number =
123 seq_unwrapper_.UnwrapWithoutUpdate(packet.SequenceNumber());
124
125 if (!ReceivedRtpPacket()) {
126 received_seq_first_ = sequence_number;
127 last_report_seq_max_ = sequence_number - 1;
128 received_seq_max_ = sequence_number - 1;
129 receive_counters_.first_packet_time_ms = now_ms;
130 } else if (UpdateOutOfOrder(packet, sequence_number, now_ms)) {
131 return;
132 }
133 // In order packet.
134 cumulative_loss_ += sequence_number - received_seq_max_;
135 received_seq_max_ = sequence_number;
136 seq_unwrapper_.UpdateLast(sequence_number);
137
138 // If new time stamp and more than one in-order packet received, calculate
139 // new jitter statistics.
140 if (packet.Timestamp() != last_received_timestamp_ &&
141 (receive_counters_.transmitted.packets -
142 receive_counters_.retransmitted.packets) > 1) {
143 UpdateJitter(packet, now_ms);
144 }
145 last_received_timestamp_ = packet.Timestamp();
146 last_receive_time_ms_ = now_ms;
147}
148
149void StreamStatisticianImpl::UpdateJitter(const RtpPacketReceived& packet,
150 int64_t receive_time_ms) {
151 int64_t receive_diff_ms = receive_time_ms - last_receive_time_ms_;
152 RTC_DCHECK_GE(receive_diff_ms, 0);
153 uint32_t receive_diff_rtp = static_cast<uint32_t>(
154 (receive_diff_ms * packet.payload_type_frequency()) / 1000);
155 int32_t time_diff_samples =
156 receive_diff_rtp - (packet.Timestamp() - last_received_timestamp_);
157
158 time_diff_samples = std::abs(time_diff_samples);
159
160 // lib_jingle sometimes deliver crazy jumps in TS for the same stream.
161 // If this happens, don't update jitter value. Use 5 secs video frequency
162 // as the threshold.
163 if (time_diff_samples < 450000) {
164 // Note we calculate in Q4 to avoid using float.
165 int32_t jitter_diff_q4 = (time_diff_samples << 4) - jitter_q4_;
166 jitter_q4_ += ((jitter_diff_q4 + 8) >> 4);
167 }
168}

172 max_reordering_threshold_ = max_reordering_threshold;
173}

175void StreamStatisticianImpl::EnableRetransmitDetection(bool enable) {
176 enable_retransmit_detection_ = enable;
177}
178
179RtpReceiveStats StreamStatisticianImpl::GetStats() const {
180 RtpReceiveStats stats;
181 stats.packets_lost = cumulative_loss_;
182 // TODO(nisse): Can we return a float instead?
183 // Note: internal jitter value is in Q4 and needs to be scaled by 1/16.
184 stats.jitter = jitter_q4_ >> 4;
185 if (receive_counters_.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms.has_value()) {
186 stats.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms =
187 *receive_counters_.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms +
188 delta_internal_unix_epoch_ms_;
189 }
190 stats.packet_counter = receive_counters_.transmitted;
191 return stats;
192}
193
194void StreamStatisticianImpl::MaybeAppendReportBlockAndReset(
195 std::vector<rtcp::ReportBlock>& report_blocks) {
196 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
197 if (now_ms - last_receive_time_ms_ >= kStatisticsTimeoutMs) {
198 // Not active.
199 return;
200 }
201 if (!ReceivedRtpPacket()) {
202 return;
203 }
204
205 report_blocks.emplace_back();
206 rtcp::ReportBlock& stats = report_blocks.back();
207 stats.SetMediaSsrc(ssrc_);
208 // Calculate fraction lost.
209 int64_t exp_since_last = received_seq_max_ - last_report_seq_max_;
210 RTC_DCHECK_GE(exp_since_last, 0);
211
212 int32_t lost_since_last = cumulative_loss_ - last_report_cumulative_loss_;
213 if (exp_since_last > 0 && lost_since_last > 0) {
214 // Scale 0 to 255, where 255 is 100% loss.
215 stats.SetFractionLost(255 * lost_since_last / exp_since_last);
216 }
217
218 int packets_lost = cumulative_loss_ + cumulative_loss_rtcp_offset_;
219 if (packets_lost < 0) {
220 // Clamp to zero. Work around to accomodate for senders that misbehave with
221 // negative cumulative loss.
222 packets_lost = 0;
223 cumulative_loss_rtcp_offset_ = -cumulative_loss_;
224 }
225 if (packets_lost > 0x7fffff) {
226 // Packets lost is a 24 bit signed field, and thus should be clamped, as
227 // described in https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc3550#appendix-A.3
228 if (!cumulative_loss_is_capped_) {
229 cumulative_loss_is_capped_ = true;
230 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Cumulative loss reached maximum value for ssrc "
231 << ssrc_;
232 }
233 packets_lost = 0x7fffff;
234 }
235 stats.SetCumulativeLost(packets_lost);
236 stats.SetExtHighestSeqNum(received_seq_max_);
237 // Note: internal jitter value is in Q4 and needs to be scaled by 1/16.
238 stats.SetJitter(jitter_q4_ >> 4);
239
240 // Only for report blocks in RTCP SR and RR.
241 last_report_cumulative_loss_ = cumulative_loss_;
242 last_report_seq_max_ = received_seq_max_;
243 BWE_TEST_LOGGING_PLOT_WITH_SSRC(1, "cumulative_loss_pkts", now_ms,
244 cumulative_loss_, ssrc_);
245 BWE_TEST_LOGGING_PLOT_WITH_SSRC(1, "received_seq_max_pkts", now_ms,
246 (received_seq_max_ - received_seq_first_),
247 ssrc_);
248}
249
250absl::optional<int> StreamStatisticianImpl::GetFractionLostInPercent() const {
251 if (!ReceivedRtpPacket()) {
252 return absl::nullopt;
253 }
254 int64_t expected_packets = 1 + received_seq_max_ - received_seq_first_;
255 if (expected_packets <= 0) {
256 return absl::nullopt;
257 }
258 if (cumulative_loss_ <= 0) {
259 return 0;
260 }
261 return 100 * static_cast<int64_t>(cumulative_loss_) / expected_packets;
262}

272
273bool StreamStatisticianImpl::IsRetransmitOfOldPacket(
274 const RtpPacketReceived& packet,
275 int64_t now_ms) const {
276 uint32_t frequency_khz = packet.payload_type_frequency() / 1000;
277 RTC_DCHECK_GT(frequency_khz, 0);
278
279 int64_t time_diff_ms = now_ms - last_receive_time_ms_;
280
281 // Diff in time stamp since last received in order.
282 uint32_t timestamp_diff = packet.Timestamp() - last_received_timestamp_;
283 uint32_t rtp_time_stamp_diff_ms = timestamp_diff / frequency_khz;
284
285 int64_t max_delay_ms = 0;
286
287 // Jitter standard deviation in samples.
288 float jitter_std = std::sqrt(static_cast<float>(jitter_q4_ >> 4));
289
290 // 2 times the standard deviation => 95% confidence.
291 // And transform to milliseconds by dividing by the frequency in kHz.
292 max_delay_ms = static_cast<int64_t>((2 * jitter_std) / frequency_khz);
293
294 // Min max_delay_ms is 1.
295 if (max_delay_ms == 0) {
296 max_delay_ms = 1;
297 }
298 return time_diff_ms > rtp_time_stamp_diff_ms + max_delay_ms;
299}

301std::unique_ptr<ReceiveStatistics> ReceiveStatistics::Create(Clock* clock) {
302 return std::make_unique<ReceiveStatisticsLocked>(
303 clock, [](uint32_t ssrc, Clock* clock, int max_reordering_threshold) {
304 return std::make_unique<StreamStatisticianLocked>(
305 ssrc, clock, max_reordering_threshold);
306 });
307}
308
309std::unique_ptr<ReceiveStatistics> ReceiveStatistics::CreateThreadCompatible(
310 Clock* clock) {
311 return std::make_unique<ReceiveStatisticsImpl>(
312 clock, [](uint32_t ssrc, Clock* clock, int max_reordering_threshold) {
313 return std::make_unique<StreamStatisticianImpl>(
314 ssrc, clock, max_reordering_threshold);
315 });
316}
317
318ReceiveStatisticsImpl::ReceiveStatisticsImpl(
319 Clock* clock,
320 std::function<std::unique_ptr<StreamStatisticianImplInterface>(
321 uint32_t ssrc,
322 Clock* clock,
323 int max_reordering_threshold)> stream_statistician_factory)
324 : clock_(clock),
325 stream_statistician_factory_(std::move(stream_statistician_factory)),
326 last_returned_ssrc_idx_(0),
327 max_reordering_threshold_(kDefaultMaxReorderingThreshold) {}
328
329void ReceiveStatisticsImpl::OnRtpPacket(const RtpPacketReceived& packet) {
330 // StreamStatisticianImpl instance is created once and only destroyed when
331 // this whole ReceiveStatisticsImpl is destroyed. StreamStatisticianImpl has
332 // it's own locking so don't hold receive_statistics_lock_ (potential
333 // deadlock).
334 GetOrCreateStatistician(packet.Ssrc())->UpdateCounters(packet);
335}
336
337StreamStatistician* ReceiveStatisticsImpl::GetStatistician(
338 uint32_t ssrc) const {
339 const auto& it = statisticians_.find(ssrc);
340 if (it == statisticians_.end())
341 return nullptr;
342 return it->second.get();
343}
344
345StreamStatisticianImplInterface* ReceiveStatisticsImpl::GetOrCreateStatistician(
346 uint32_t ssrc) {
347 std::unique_ptr<StreamStatisticianImplInterface>& impl = statisticians_[ssrc];
348 if (impl == nullptr) { // new element
349 impl =
350 stream_statistician_factory_(ssrc, clock_, max_reordering_threshold_);
351 all_ssrcs_.push_back(ssrc);
352 }
353 return impl.get();
354}
355
356void ReceiveStatisticsImpl::SetMaxReorderingThreshold(
357 int max_reordering_threshold) {
358 max_reordering_threshold_ = max_reordering_threshold;
359 for (auto& statistician : statisticians_) {
360 statistician.second->SetMaxReorderingThreshold(max_reordering_threshold);
361 }
362}
363
364void ReceiveStatisticsImpl::SetMaxReorderingThreshold(
365 uint32_t ssrc,
366 int max_reordering_threshold) {
367 GetOrCreateStatistician(ssrc)->SetMaxReorderingThreshold(
368 max_reordering_threshold);
369}
370
371void ReceiveStatisticsImpl::EnableRetransmitDetection(uint32_t ssrc,
372 bool enable) {
373 GetOrCreateStatistician(ssrc)->EnableRetransmitDetection(enable);
374}
375
376std::vector<rtcp::ReportBlock> ReceiveStatisticsImpl::RtcpReportBlocks(
377 size_t max_blocks) {
378 std::vector<rtcp::ReportBlock> result;
379 result.reserve(std::min(max_blocks, all_ssrcs_.size()));
380
381 size_t ssrc_idx = 0;
382 for (size_t i = 0; i < all_ssrcs_.size() && result.size() < max_blocks; ++i) {
383 ssrc_idx = (last_returned_ssrc_idx_ + i + 1) % all_ssrcs_.size();
384 const uint32_t media_ssrc = all_ssrcs_[ssrc_idx];
385 auto statistician_it = statisticians_.find(media_ssrc);
386 RTC_DCHECK(statistician_it != statisticians_.end());
387 statistician_it->second->MaybeAppendReportBlockAndReset(result);
388 }
389 last_returned_ssrc_idx_ = ssrc_idx;
390 return result;
391}
